 support of Operation Iraqi Freedom from 2003 2004 where he conducted combat missions in the city of Ar Ramadi in the volatile Anbar Province  Upon return  SSG Borawski was reassigned to the Syracuse Recruiting Battalion where he served as a Recruiter in Rochester  NY from 2005 2008  Afterwards he was then assigned to 1st Armored Division at Fort Bliss  TX  First we was assigned to their 4th Brigade  Highlanders  where he continued his duties as a tank crewman with Delta Company  Dogs of War  1st Battalion 77th Armor Regiment  Steel Tigers  He deployed two more times to Iraq with 1 77  this time to the Muthanna Province in Southern Iraq where he continued stability and transition operations  Upon return  SSG Borawski was reassigned over to 1 AD s 1st Brigade  1st Stryker Brigade Combat Team  where he was now Vehicle Commander on a Mobile Gun System for 1st Battalion  36th Infantry Regiment  Spartans  He deployed to Afghanistan in the Maiwand District of the Kandahar Province with 1 36 IN in support of combat operations  His military training includes Armor One Station Unit Training  US Army Recruiting School  Warrior Leader s Course  Advanced Leader s Course  and Maneuver Senior Leader s Course  He is currently pursuing his Bachelor s Degree in Business Administration Sports Management from Columbia Southern University  His military awards and decorations include  Purple Heart  Army Commendation Medal with Silver Oak Leaf Cluster  Army Achievement Medal with 4 Oak Leaf Clusters  Army Good Conduct Medal with 4 knots  National Defense Service Medal  Armed Forces Expeditionary Medal  Afghanistan Campaign Medal with 1 campaign star  Iraq Campaign Medal with 2 campaign stars  Global War on Terrorism Expeditionary Medal  Global War on Terrorism Service Medal  Noncommissioned Officer Professional Development Ribbon with  3  device  Army Service Ribbon  Overseas Service Ribbon with  4  device  NATO Ribbon  Gold Recruiter Badge  and the Combat Action Badge    VMI Foundation 